Ohio State Suspends Coach Tressel for Two Games Over NCAA Infractions

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-03-09T00:15:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/ohio-state-suspends-coach-tressel-for-two-games-over-ncaa-infractions.html
  Ohio State University  suspended
football coach Jim Tressel for two games for failing to disclose
that he knew quarterback Terrelle Pryor and other players were
violating National Collegiate Athletic Association rules eight
months before the school said it was informed of the
infractions.  Athletic Director Gene Smith announced the suspension
during a televised news conference today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  